The Factory Method Pattern is a design pattern used to create objects 
without directly using new in the client code.

Factory Method Pattern is a creational design pattern 
that creates objects through a factory class instead of 
directly using constructors. It hides object creation logic, 
reduces coupling, and makes the code easier to extend and maintain.


Document.java
public interface Document {

    
    void open();

   
    void save();

   
    void close();
}


WordDocument.java
class WordDocument implements Document {

    @Override
    public void open() {
        System.out.println("[WordDocument] Opening Word document (.docx)...");
    }

    @Override
    public void save() {
        System.out.println("[WordDocument] Saving Word document (.docx)...");
    }

    @Override
    public void close() {
        System.out.println("[WordDocument] Closing Word document (.docx).");
    }
}

